    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.8.15" />
                <fw type="curatorial">15</fw>
<opener>                
<dateline>Branson, Mo., 3/2/22.</dateline>

<salute>Dear Mott:</salute>
</opener>
<p>Idaho is seriously considering state adoption of <hi rend="underline">Hugh Glass.</hi> <hi rend="italic">You</hi> can help tremendously, and I believe you will. Do you care to write a letter to Miss Redfield State Supt. of Public Instruction, Boise, Idaho, stating that you have heard of the possibilities in Idaho + telling of the results you have obtained with <hi rend="underline">Glass</hi>? Also, could you not get others to do likewise - Mrs. Brown of Indianola, for instance?</p>

<p>If I can ever be of service to you, be sure that I shall regard the opportunity as a source of genuine pleasure.</p>
<closer>
<salute>Yours,</salute>

<signed>Jno. N.</signed>
</closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
        
